
Overview of verb curtail

The verb curtail has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (5) restrict, curtail, curb, cut back -- (place restrictions on; "curtail drinking in school")
2. clip, curtail, cut short -- (terminate or abbreviate before its intended or proper end or its full extent; "My speech was cut short"; "Personal freedom is curtailed in many countries")
